The application for the 2024-2025 White House Fellows Program is now open. The program, founded in 1964, offers exceptional Americans the opportunity to work at the highest levels of the Federal Government on a non-partisan basis. Selected individuals spend one year in Washington, D.C., working as full-time paid government employees, assisting Cabinet Secretaries, senior White House staff, and other top-ranking government officials. The program has produced many successful alumni who have gone on to top positions in various fields. The application deadline is January 5, 2024. Interested individuals can apply at fellows.whitehouse.gov and find more information at whitehouse.gov/get-involved/fellows. Any questions can be directed to whitehousefellows@who.eop.gov.